            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EThe%20psalmist%20declares%20a%20holy%20revulsion%20that%20must%20dwell%20in%20your%20heart%20against%20anything%20that%20challenges%20the%20law%20of%20God.%20If%20you%20consistently%20struggle%20to%20conquer%20an%20area%20of%20sin%20in%20your%20life%2C%20it%20may%20be%20that%20you%20do%20not%20hate%20that%20sin.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EOne%20sin%20God%20hates%20is%20divorce%20(Malachi%202%3A16)%2C%20not%20because%20He%20wants%20to%20be%20legalistic%20but%20because%20He%20knows%20the%20terrible%20consequences%20you%20will%20suffer%20from%20it.%20Satan's%20deception%20concerning%20this%20sin%20and%20all%20sin%20is%20so%20devious%20and%20the%20consequences%20of%20disobedience%20so%20eternal%20that%20you%20must%20develop%20a%20passion%20against%20all%20sin%2C%20for%20it%20destroys%20people's%20souls.%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EDouble-minded%20or%20undecided%20people%20(Psalm%20119%3A113)%20are%20those%20who%20mix%20God's%20law%20with%20their%20own%20reasoning%2C%20listening%20to%20the%20voice%20of%20personal%20opinion%20rather%20than%20the%20voice%20of%20truth.%20Such%20compromisers%20lead%20the%20godly%20astray%20and%20are%20unstable%20in%20all%20their%20ways%20(James%201%3A8).%20If%20you%20are%20double-minded%2C%20rid%20yourself%20of%20lukewarmness%2C%20and%20purify%20your%20heart.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIf%20you%20don't%20hate%20sin%2C%20you%20will%20fall%20into%20it.%20Love%20God%20and%20hate%20sin%2C%20and%20you%20will%20always%20walk%20in%20the%20path%20of%20righteousness.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
